# MernCrest Part 05 — ERP & Internal Operations

Continue from Parts 01–04. Do **not** redesign or remove existing ERP, CRM, portal, or commerce modules.

## Core rule

The ERP is the **internal operating system** for MernCrest and must stay **multi-tenant ready** (Organization → Branch) for future SaaS customers.

Every ERP module must integrate with:

- CRM
- Finance
- HR / ESS
- Notifications
- Reports / Analytics
- Audit Logs

Never duplicate business logic — reuse shared libs (`lib/erp/*`, `lib/crm/*`, `writeAuditLog`, approval hub).

## Module map

Hub: `/admin/erp` · Staff ESS: `/staff`

Key surfaces: Organization · HRM · Finance · COA · Approvals · Procurement · Inventory · SCM · Manufacturing · Assets · ESM · FSM · Projects · CSM (Support) · IoT · Maintenance · AI · BI · DMS · Audit · Permissions · Dashboards

## Organization

`Organization` + `Branch` + `Department` + Employees + org roles.

Primary tenant: MernCrest (`MCS`). Additional orgs = SaaS tenants later.

## Approvals & audit

- Leave / PO / expense / quote / project / invoice → `ApprovalRequest`
- All material mutations → `writeAuditLog` (`AuditLog`)
- Notifications on approval assign / decide

## Finance foundation

`ChartOfAccount` seeds default GL structure. Finance entries, payroll slips (`SalarySlip`), and AR/AP deepen on this COA — do not invent parallel ledgers.

## ESS (Employee Self-Service)

`/staff`: profile, tasks, leave, salary slips, approvals, notifications, internal chat.

## Permissions

Granular `erp.*.view|manage` + org roles (CEO → Auditor). Use `requirePermission` / `permission-matrix` presets. Prefer grant/revoke over hard-coding roles in UI.

## Security & data

UUID/cuid PKs · soft delete where present (`deletedAt`) · actor fields via audit · RBAC · department isolation where modeled.

## APIs

REST under `/api/erp/*` with validation, pagination/filtering where lists exist, audit on writes, version-friendly shapes.
